8:
Well, Keira? How about we leave the
rest of this work for tomorrow and
go enjoy this lovely weather?
12:
Hmph. Nice try, but you're not going
anywhere.
16:
You KNOW we have a mountain of
paperwork that needs your
approval, captain.
20:
Can't you just handle it on your
own? You don't need to ask me for
every little thing.
24:
If I recall correctly, the last time you
said that, Commander Finn
demolished your smoking room.
28:
He's a ruthless one, I'll give him that.
Well, I suppose it got me to quit
smoking.
32:
...I'm surprised you managed to stick
to that particular resolution.
36:
Well, my girl doesn't seem to like the
smell.
40:
Your girl? Are you talking about Dul
Kugala? Hm... Mind telling me more?
44: Whoa there, it's not what you think—
47:
Ah, that reminds me. I got a job from
her.
50:
It's about the attack on the
ceremony celebrating our
partnership with the Farlands.
They're moving Orgus Oxtan to the
Farlands.
59:
To send him home, I guess. That's
what the Farlands want, and the
Guild is willing to do it.
62:
But he still hasn't given us any solid
information!
66:
And what exactly will happen when
he does?
69:
If it turns out that the rogue who
interrupted the long-awaited
partnership with Palpebra was
actually working with the Farlands...
71:
...I'm just saying some rocks are best
left unturned. Unless you want to
change the Guild Knights into the
Guild Spies.
74:
The wha—what are you going on
about?
78:
Rumors have been circulating since
the ceremony. The timing of the
attack was just too perfect...
81:
Anyway, unless you want to trade
guard duty with espionage in a
foreign land, I'd just smile and keep
your head down.
84:
Hold on, don't tell me you WANT to
be a spy. Look, you've got the skills,
but—
88:
That man has connections to the
group Commander Finn is pursuing.
Surely our ongoing investigation has
some importance.
96:
Okay, okay, I get it. I know you've got
your reasons for being against this,
so I'll see what I can do.
101:
Anyway, I've got some negotiating
to do, so I'll leave the rest of this
paperwork to you.
103:
Don't worry, I'm sure overtime won't
feel so bad with your beloved
commander by your side.
112: All right, Finn, I leave the rest to you.
129:
I see, so you will be escorting Orgus
yourself...
132:
Yeah, I figured it'd be a good idea to
introduce myself to the people of
the Farlands.
134:
Besides, it'd be a real problem if one
of our key suspects suddenly
disappeared or was disposed of.
138:
True... With you on the job, such
worries are trivial. Are you sure
about this, though?
141:
My happy-go-lucky days sitting
behind a desk aren't going to last
forever.
143:
Besides, I prefer to pick my battles
myself over having things sprung on
me.
147:
I very much doubt anyone would try
anything with you around.
155:
In any case, I graciously accept your
proposal. Although, I suppose that
means some introductions are in
order.
159: This man will also be acting as escor—
166: What is the meaning of this?
170:
Didn't expect to see YOU here,
Velgar Solon...
175:
Likewise. What's the deal, kid? You
never told me this dog was gonna
be here.
179:
I believe I told you not to call me
that. I am a sheephird, not a child.
183:
Got a little carried away there. My
bad, my bad.
185:
I just didn't expect to see the face of
the man I've been pursuing for the
past decade. It took me back to the
old days...
189:
Seriously, I apologize. Think we can
let bygones be bygones?
194: After you damn near slit my throat?
198:
Come on now, I could say the same
thing about you.
204:
...I believe it is illegal to draw
weapons inside Guild
establishments, is it not?
214:
Just my luck. Of course the ghosts of
the past would pop up just when I
chose to get involved...
217:
The assassination of Etheria Nialas. I
believe that was when you decided
to become a knight, correct? That
must be over thirty years ago now...
222:
Nah, I just wanted a steadier
paycheck than what I was getting
as an adventurer.
226:
Yes, yes. Let's just pretend I believe
that.
230:
I really did step in it this time though.
This is a bigger job than I thought.
233:
Don't you think now would be a
good time to tell me about your
friends?
236:
I promised I would not tell a soul
about them or their base. But if you
want me to introduce you, I'm sure I
could discuss that with them.
239:
Hm... I was hoping you could tell me
without involving them.
243: No can do. I made a promise.
247:
Fine. Then can I have you set up
something once I get back?
256:
Alk and Stella, was it? I wonder what
they're like.
259:
Aren't you going to ask me how I
know their names?
262:
No, I was just wondering who you
could possibly be talking about.
266:
Ha! You're too smart for your own
good...
